caption.text:
CONDIVIDI NELLE STORIE ⬇️ SoulCalibur non è sulla cresta dell'onda da molti anni, e tanti sono i franchise, vecchi e nuovi, che negli ultimi tempi sono riusciti a catalizzare l'attenzione al suo posto. Tuttavia, è bene ricordare il ruolo di rilievo ricoperto in passato. In particolare, oggi celebriamo l'anniversario di SoulCalibur II - effettivamente terza installazione del franchise - il quale non è ricordato solo per i numerosi "punteggi perfetti" da parte della critica, ma per l'affetto che gli appassionati nutrono nei suoi confronti (tanto da essere oggetto di una rimasterizzazione abilitata al gioco in rete nel 2013). SoulCalibur II, nato in ambito arcade analogamente ad altri picchiaduro, portava avanti quanto era stato premiato del primo capitolo con relativamente poche novità sul fronte ludico. Poche, ma fondamentali, come i muri ai bordi dell'arena, le mosse specifiche da eseguire in loro prossimità, gli stati post-impatto da guardia, gli effetti per l'attacco congiunto e tanti aggiustamenti minori. Sebbene dall'esterno non fossero tutte immediatamente palesi, per chi mastica i fondamenti del picchiaduro competitivo, questi piccoli aggiustamenti sono come la panna sulla cioccolata calda. 
Per tutti gli altri giocatori, quelli meno impegnati - da salotto, della domenica, o semplicemente appassionati ma non competitivi - c'era l'innovazione tecnologica. Era il 2002, erano passati 4 anni da SoulCalibur e 7 da Soul Blade, e con PlayStation 2, GameCube, ma soprattutto Xbox, ci si poteva permettere di basare il 'fattore novità' sul mero sviluppo tecnico. Non si trattava solamente di effetti migliori, ma di una resa migliore degli ambienti e dei personaggi - i quali, a nostro avviso, rappresentano l'elemento più interessante del franchise.

caption.text:
NINTENDO SWITCH LITE.
Консоль для тех, кто любит играть в пути.

Nintendo Switch Lite — новое пополнение в семействе Nintendo Switch. Компактная и легкая консоль со встроенным управлением.

Nintendo Switch Lite поддерживает все игры Nintendo Switch, в которые можно играть в портативном режиме. Консоль отлично подойдет для тех, кто много играет вне дома, и для тех, кто хочет играть в сетевом или локальном мультиплеере с друзьями и родными, у которых уже есть флагманская модель Nintendo Switch.

Консоль Nintendo Switch Lite предназначена для портативного гейминга, поэтому ее нельзя подключить к телевизору. ⚠️В НАЛИЧИИ В МАГАЗИНЕ @digitalhouse_minsk !

caption.text:
Untitled Goose Game is here and it is HILARIOUS! Definitely a contender for GOTY (Goose Of The Year) 😍 Have you played the Goose game yet??⁣
⁣
I had so much fun with this silly little game! It's the perfect mix of clever problem solving and chaotic action and it had me grinning from start to end. The minimalistic art style is just so pretty to look at! And the music is fantastic, the way it picks up and slows down to match the action of the game was done so well. I definitely recommend playing Untitled Goose Game on a TV with friends or family around because it's just as fun to watch as it is to play 🥰⁣
⁣
My only complaint about the game is that I want more of it 😅 It only takes around 3 hours to complete all the main tasks but there are some bonus tasks at the end to give you more reason to mess around. I still think it's totally worth it though, especially because it's on a launch sale atm for 25% off 💕✨

Trainers,

Happy World Tourism Day! In partnership with the United Nations World Tourism Organisation (UNWTO), we are celebrating the first-ever World Tourism Day event in Pokémon GO! For this upcoming week, we’ll be celebrating exploration with a special in-game event.

New features starting on September 26, 2019 at 1 p.m. PDT (GMT −7)

New shirt! Check out a new United Nations World Tourism Organization T-shirt, available in the Style Shop!
Region-limited Pokémon available in Eggs! The following Pokémon will be available in 5 km Eggs in their respective real-world regions: Farfetch’d, Kangaskhan, Tauros, Heracross, Corsola, Volbeat, Illumise, Torkoal, Zangoose, Seviper, Lunatone, Solrock, Tropius, Relicanth, Pachirisu, Mime Jr., Chatot, Pansage, Pansear, Panpour, Heatmor, and Durant.
Shiny Pokémon rivals spotted! If you’re lucky, you might encounter a Shiny Zangoose or a Shiny Seviper in the wild in their respective real-world regions!
Mime Jr., the Mime Pokémon, will be making its debut in Pokémon GO! It will be available in 5 km Eggs in Europe. If you’re lucky, you might hatch a Shiny Mime Jr.!
Features from Thursday, September 26, 2019, at 1 p.m. PDT (GMT −7) to Tuesday, October 1, 2019, at 1 p.m. PDT (GMT −7)

Decreased Stardust costs for trading! Trading Pokémon will cost 1/4 less Stardust.
Spin PokéStops for extra XP! Earn 2× XP when you spin the Photo Discs of PokéStops you haven’t visited before.
Specially themed Field Research tasks will be available for a limited time during this event.
Credits @leekduck and @pokemongoapp

preview_comments.text: Tough question... I love Zelda but Yoshi is my favourite character and he appears in Mario games. Can I choose both? 😂

caption.text:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
× ᴡʜɪᴄʜ ɢᴀᴍᴇꜱ ᴅᴏ ʏᴏᴜ ᴘʀᴇꜰᴇʀ, ʟᴇɢᴇɴᴅ ᴏꜰ ᴢᴇʟᴅᴀ ᴏʀ ꜱᴜᴘᴇʀ ᴍᴀʀɪᴏ? ×
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
☆ I'm a massive fan of both the LoZ & Mario games & I know there isn't really any comparison since they're two different styles of games, but if I had to pick one to keep & the other to never play again, I'd be keeping the LoZ. 
Don't get me wrong, I have so many fond memories of playing Mario games as a kid, and they were a massive part of me getting into gaming, but the LoZ games literally consumed me when I played them & gave me a world I felt I could escape too & I never get tired or bored of playing them. I think each one is a masterpiece in it's own right ☆

caption.text:
I was barely a teenager when I first saw #DragonsLair in the 'Playtime' video game arcade next to the Hoyts cinema in Charlestown, NSW.

It was simply the most stunning game I'd ever seen and thought there was no way game developers could never make anything better. 😝 Remember, at this point in history, a Commodore 64 was the height of home gaming technology. 
Dragon's Lair was also a jaw-dropping $2 per credit, when most games at the time were just 60c or $1 a go. I sucked at the game and would quickly burn my pocket money within 15 minutes of arriving. But I didn't care... I WAS CONTROLLING (BADLY) A CARTOON! 
And now, three and a half decades later, here it is - complete with its sequels - on a game cartridge not much larger than a postage stamp. What a time to be alive. 😌

قد أصبحت ذهبية وجاهزة للإطلاق في نفس موعد الإصدار ولن يتم تأجيلها ✨
وعبر عن فرحته كوجيما عبر حسابه الرسمي في التويتر عن لعبته وقال:

.
